      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DEEPFLOAT DIVA (3) is a much better gelding than his two runs back so far suggest. Will appreciate getting his toe into it third-up and has trialled well in-between runs. His best puts them away. PURE BLISS (5) was a smart winner fresh here when darting up the fence but is yet to go on with it. Had excuses last time when pulling up lame. Gets in well with the 3kg claim and is worth keeping onside. HALLIWELL (4) returns and is a noted wet tracker. Draws well for Pannell and has the benefit of two hitouts. Can play a role fresh. OMAHA DAWN (9) was a good winner over this track and trip when resuming back in March. Has been solid since and keeps Holder. In the mix.",
